
[1]camisade

   CAMISADE, n. An attack by surprise, at night, or at break of day, when
   the enemy is supposed to be in bed. This word is said to have taken its
   rise from an attack of this kind, in which the soldiers, as a badge to
   distinguish each other by, bore a shirt over their arms.
